    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the narrator's intent in its historical and canonical context. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from the opening summary statement through the mourning that closes it. Where the Hebrew idiom or syntax sharpens the English, a brief note supplements the interpretation.",
